Consistency vs Availability (CAP) — Banking (15 min)


Excellent 👍 This is core distributed system theory and very important for banking + interviews.

CAP Theorem — Consistency vs Availability (Banking)
What is CAP Theorem?

In a distributed system, you cannot guarantee all three at the same time:

C — Consistency

A — Availability

P — Partition Tolerance

👉 You can choose only 2 out of 3.

Since network failures (Partition) are unavoidable → You must choose between C or A.

1️⃣ Consistency (C)

Every read gets the latest correct data.

Example:

Balance = ₹10,000

After transfer → Balance must be ₹9,000 everywhere immediately

No stale data allowed ✔

2️⃣ Availability (A)

System must always respond — even during failure.

Even if data is slightly outdated, system should not fail.

Example:

ATM should still show balance even if DB replica lagging

3️⃣ Partition Tolerance (P)

System continues working even if network breaks between nodes.

Example:

Account DB node disconnected

System must still operate

👉 In real systems, Partition is unavoidable → P is always required

So Choice = CP or AP
Banking System → CP (Consistency + Partition)

Banking cannot tolerate wrong data.

If system must choose:

Option	Result
Available but wrong balance	❌ Not acceptable
Temporarily unavailable but correct	✔ Acceptable

👉 Banking chooses Consistency over Availability

Real Banking Example
Case: Transfer ₹1000

Two servers:

Server A → Debit

Server B → Credit

Network failure occurs.

If AP (Availability priority)

Debit happens

Credit fails

Money lost ❌

If CP (Consistency priority)

Transaction blocked

No partial update

System may delay response ✔

CP Systems in Real World

Banking

Payment systems (UPI, Visa)

Order processing (financial)

Inventory control

AP Systems (Availability priority)

Used when eventual consistency acceptable

Social media likes

Notifications

Analytics

Chat apps

Strong vs Eventual Consistency
Strong Consistency (Banking)

Immediately correct data everywhere.

Eventual Consistency (Social media)

Data sync after few seconds.

